<subSubSection id="F4DC02DBB9F5999DF3F507AF2AAE2A22" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BC3BB4E85FACB84964F5306209C949D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A15CBD8CBD739CED407A73FB6FE87A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
The description of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="C9333E911A6404B5841B53F835F3E76B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" author="Eberhardt, U" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="172 - 184" refId="B11" refString="Eberhardt, U, Beker, HJ, Schuetz, N, Pedersen, OS, Sysouphanthong, P, Laessoe, T, 2020. Adventurous cuisine in Laos: Hebeloma parvisporum, a new species in Hebeloma section Porphyrospora. Mycologia 112 (1): 172 - 184, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" title="Adventurous cuisine in Laos: Hebeloma parvisporum, a new species in Hebeloma section Porphyrospora." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2019.1680220" volume="112" year="2020">Eberhardt et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) was based upon the above collections from Laos. The intended holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="3FE2619A4CA864B90DBA212DF8931185" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. splendens" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="9537571FBC73007CC058BD7C6E7588E0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">P. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was examined and is micro- and macromorphologically in agreement with 
<taxonomicName id="0E98245C932B7D7692732B35BB419C68" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. parvisporum" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvisporum">
<emphasis id="025AC3B6A32BD056B2808A5BD518A5CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. parvisporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this is illustrated in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8C2AF152DAF8FBBBB1AF3DED15AA73EF" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Microscopic features of Hebeloma parvisporum (E 00204835; intended holotype of Psathyrella splendens nom. inval.) A spores in Melzer's reagent x 1600 B spore ornamentation in Melzer's reagent x 1600 C, D cheilocystidia in KOH x 1000 E cheilocystidia and basidium in KOH x 500 F caulocystidia, in KOH x 1000. Scale bars: 10 µm. Photos H. J. Beker. G Exsiccata (a section of photograph from http: // data. rbge. org. uk / herb / E 00204835, provided by the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.77.57394.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502276" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">7</figureCitation>
which shows the main micro characters of 
<normalizedToken id="DE5593DF3B9D5BA55C7941A124C6F0F6" originalValue="Corner’s">Corner's</normalizedToken>
intended type. The collection from Malaysia is monophyletic with the Laos material. Molecularly, the species is most closely related to the Australian/New Zealand 
<taxonomicName id="C70925289997AD1357CCAD27F3A3B0AD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. victoriense" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="victoriense">
<emphasis id="9E171027772BA537EF7A3B5C6546C545" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. victoriense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C53F1B1B0500A80CAF45374D0133B17D" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
The collection cited as holotype for 
<taxonomicName id="DCE65C865F60EBDC92A1F2D6E4448182" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. splendens" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="4F22E39226B2B9D04E892305BFBB7C34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">P. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in Singapore while Corner also cites other collections from Singapore and Malaysia (
<bibRefCitation id="E52F7FD00C88E7DEC741AD03AE367576" author="Corner, EJH" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" publicationUrl="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" refId="B8" refString="Corner, EJH, 1994 [&quot;1993&quot;]. Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337-357. https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" title="Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337 - 357." url="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" year="1994 [&quot; 1993 &quot;]">
Corner 1994 [
<normalizedToken id="57994A28566C326E03F741068D6355F9" originalValue="“1993”">&quot;1993&quot;</normalizedToken>
]
</bibRefCitation>
), to which we can add the Malaysian collection above. Plate 3 of 
<bibRefCitation id="2159C405A3BCA09A4A230AA4DE07CFCF" author="Corner, EJH" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" publicationUrl="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" refId="B8" refString="Corner, EJH, 1994 [&quot;1993&quot;]. Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337-357. https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" title="Psathyrella (Agaricales) with ornamented spores in the Malay Peninsula. Gardens Bulletin Singapore 45: 337 - 357." url="https://www.nparks.gov.sg/sbg/research/publications/gardens-bulletin-singapore/-/media/sbg/gardens-bulletin/4-4-45-2-02-y1993-v45p2-gbs-pg-337.pdf" year="1994 [&quot; 1993 &quot;]">
Corner (1994 [
<normalizedToken id="03B9748E4F2842F70CC872765E3CB85F" originalValue="“1993”">&quot;1993&quot;</normalizedToken>
])
</bibRefCitation>
illustrates the species macroscopically; 
<bibRefCitation id="F59B9C66578193D9ADEADBBFC92A7DF7" author="Lee, SS" journalOrPublisher="Bioinformatics" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B27" refString="Lee, SS, 2017. A Field Guide to the Larger Fungi of FRIM. Forest Research Institute Malaysia, Kepong, Selangor, Malaysia." title="A Field Guide to the Larger Fungi of FRIM. Forest Research Institute Malaysia, Kepong, Selangor, Malaysia." year="2017">Lee (2017)</bibRefCitation>
includes a photograph of 
<taxonomicName id="CDB47B4F8C8786F3C63007604AB9DC9F" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. splendens" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="6AA3126829BC6F7F28392F8244A31CB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">P. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the FRIM forest and comments that it often grows in large clusters and is common in the FRIM forest and other parts of the country. The FRIM database includes additional records of this species (not studied) from: Endau-Rompin National Park, Johor; 
<normalizedToken id="C25C7073103C240179E923FF5CFCEFE3" originalValue="Fraser’s">Fraser's</normalizedToken>
Hill, Pahang; the FRIM grounds, Kepong, Selangor; Pasoh, Negeri Sembilan and Tasik Bera, Pahang from lowland and hill dipterocarp forests and a planted dipterocarp forest. S.S.L. observed this species also in degraded hill dipterocarp forest in Janda Baik, Pahang. The species is not listed on the checklist of mushrooms in Thailand (Chandrariskul et al. 2011), but Felix Hampe (oral communication, 21 Jan 2020) reported it from Thailand (Chiang Mai Prov.). Thus, it appears that this species may be widespread within tropical Asia, associated with 
<taxonomicName id="842027C1D91CC4D037512E1F2E5B1045" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
and dipterocarps (
<taxonomicName id="B6C9A9D7BE7B9CB2466D525074A9DBB1" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Dipterocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dipterocarpus" order="Guttiferales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E936AB22B0FD17943B4DEB44A8D51D84" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Dipterocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In Laos, 
<taxonomicName id="EBCFCD35BB97509771035E6C9208E530" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. parvisporum" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parvisporum">
<emphasis id="34EB93BACEE09B2374C0A524D2FFCACB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">H. parvisporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found for sale in the local markets for human consumption, but its synonym 
<taxonomicName id="4CF8689966FE8C210C47D9F5BF1584AC" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. splendens" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="D00BDD8A0B96E4CB3D86FF7BEDDFE2F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">P. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not listed among the species consumed in Malaysia (
<bibRefCitation id="7BF1EACA1BC67398A78024B18ED4E2A1" author="Chang, YS" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="15 - 22" publicationUrl="http://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/15-2.pdf" refId="B4" refString="Chang, YS, Lee, SS, 2004. Utilisation of macrofungi species in Malaysia. Fungal Diversity 15: 15 - 22, http://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/15-2.pdf" title="Utilisation of macrofungi species in Malaysia." url="http://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/15-2.pdf" volume="15" year="2004">Chang and Lee 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BD7EA1EF25228CF2E7ED1C8C9563EDD0" author="Samsudin, NIP" journalOrPublisher="International Food Research Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="11 - 31" publicationUrl="http://www.ifrj.upm.edu.my/" refId="B40" refString="Samsudin, NIP, Abdullah, N, 2019. Edible mushrooms from Malaysia; a literature review on their nutritional and medicinal properties. International Food Research Journal 26: 11 - 31, http://www.ifrj.upm.edu.my/" title="Edible mushrooms from Malaysia; a literature review on their nutritional and medicinal properties." url="http://www.ifrj.upm.edu.my/" volume="26" year="2019">Samsudin and Abdullah 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
